&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keller Postman represents a broad array of clients in class and mass actions, individual arbitrations, and multidistrict litigation matters. With a particular emphasis on large-scale arbitration proceedings, we represent hundreds of thousands of clients across mass arbitration dockets, as well as high-profile mass tort, antitrust, privacy, product liability, employment, and consumer-rights matters. Our firm also acts as plaintiffs&#39; counsel in high-stakes public-enforcement actions. Our mission is to achieve exceptional results for our clients, drive innovation in the practice of law, and pursue unparalleled excellence in everything we do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Purpose of the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are seeking a diligent, team-oriented Associate to play a key role in all phases of mass tort litigation. This individual will work closely with experienced trial lawyers on high-impact cases that make a meaningful difference in clients’ lives.&amp;nbsp;This role offers significant hands-on responsibility, exposure to complex litigation strategy, and the opportunity to contribute to large-scale, coordinated proceedings from early case development through trial. Associates may be based in our Washington, D.C., Coral Gables, Florida, or Chicago office.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;•  Evaluate and develop claims on behalf of injured clients, including factual and legal analysis&lt;br&gt;•  Review and synthesize medical records, case files, and investigatory materials&lt;br&gt;•  Draft pleadings, motions, discovery requests/responses, and legal memoranda&lt;br&gt;•  Manage written discovery and large-scale document review processes&lt;br&gt;•  Take and defend depositions of plaintiffs, fact witnesses, and expert witnesses&lt;br&gt;•  Communicate directly with clients regarding case status, expectations, and next steps&lt;br&gt;•  Collaborate with co-counsel and national litigation teams in multidistrict and coordinated proceedings&lt;br&gt;•  Assist with trial preparation, including exhibit development, witness outlines, and case strategy&lt;br&gt;•  Attend hearings, court appearances, and trials as needed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;•  Juris Doctor (JD) from an accredited law school&lt;br&gt;•  Active U.S. bar license in good standing (Illinois, D.C., or Florida preferred, depending on office location)&lt;br&gt;•  3–5 years of experience in complex litigation&lt;br&gt;•  Strong legal research, writing, and analytical skills&lt;br&gt;•  Excellent communication skills, with the ability to interact effectively with clients and colleagues&lt;br&gt;•  Ability to manage multiple priorities in a fast-paced, high-volume environment&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Preferred Qualifications:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;padding-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;•  Experience in mass torts, product liability, or personal injury litigation&lt;br&gt;•  Familiarity with multidistrict litigation (MDL), class actions, or other complex civil litigation&lt;br&gt;•  Experience reviewing and analyzing medical records&lt;br&gt;•  Exposure to expert witness development and coordination&lt;/p&gt;
