&lt;p&gt;Keller Postman delivers justice at scale.&amp;nbsp; We represent individuals and small businesses—hundreds of thousands of them—and get them compensation for harm caused by powerful corporations or the government.&amp;nbsp; We have recovered billions of dollars in litigation against some of the most sophisticated actors in the world. &amp;nbsp;Our work combines the intellectual rigor of legal practice with the innovation, pace, and scale of a tech startup.&amp;nbsp; Our firm accordingly comprises not only world-class lawyers but also distinctive developers, data scientists, designers, communications professionals, and analysts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Litigation Operations (&quot;LitOps&quot;) team sits at the heart of Keller Postman’s intense and interdisciplinary work.&amp;nbsp; Composed of former consultants, lawyers, and product managers, the team is the nexus between the firm’s litigators, technologists, and operations professionals.&amp;nbsp; We are responsible for understanding complex legal situations, translating them into concrete projects, and marshalling resources from across the firm to deliver them.&amp;nbsp; By way of example, LitOps has developed tech products used by hundreds of thousands of clients, put innovative communication tools at the fingertips of our case management team, and built AI-enabled apps to turbocharge record-review and other key legal processes.&amp;nbsp; When Keller Postman delivers justice at scale, the LitOps team contributes the “scale” part.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The LitOps team is seeking an analytical, intellectually curious, conscientious, flexible, hardworking, collaborative, and self-motivated individual to report directly to the Chief Counsel for Litigation Operations, the leader of the LitOps function.&amp;nbsp; Working across the firm’s functions, the LitOps Analyst will support and perform complex quantitative and qualitative analysis; assist in developing, building, and maintaining dashboards and other reporting; contribute to product development; coordinate large-scale communications campaigns, and more—all in the high-stakes, fast-paced environment of mass litigation.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position is in-office in our Washington, D.C., office. Compensation for this position, depending on experience, is an annual salary of $95,000 to $115,000 per year, plus benefits and a discretionary bonus.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Functions:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the Chief Counsel for Litigation Operations, Directors of Litigation operations, and LitOps Senior Analysts on mission-critical initiatives requiring detailed analysis and problem solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understand, analyze, and report on large, dispersed data sets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with LitOps colleagues, attorneys, and operations professionals in the planning, executing, and tracking client-outreach, records-collection, evidence-review, and other workstreams in support of Keller Postman’s litigation campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with external vendors hired to execute client-communication and other tasks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the design of client-facing apps, forms, and communications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Master firm technology tools (including Salesforce, Twilio, Monday.com, Azure DevOps, and proprietary tools); identify improvement opportunities and new use cases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
